# frontend core

- Reuse shared components before creating new ones. Extend existing primitives instead of introducing near-duplicate UI.
- Keep components small, purpose-specific, and explicitly typed. Avoid vague prop bags and mixed rendering/data responsibilities.
- Follow the existing design system first. Reuse shared tokens, spacing, typography, and component conventions before inventing new patterns.
- Treat Tailwind and component libraries as system tools. Use them to reinforce consistency, not to create one-off styling islands.
- Encapsulate remote data logic in dedicated hooks or clear data modules. Do not scatter fetch and mutation logic through arbitrary components.
- Use stable query keys, explicit invalidation, and explicit loading, empty, error, and success states when client-side caching is involved.
- Prefer readability, accessibility, and product consistency over cleverness or visual novelty.
